00:18:51,082 --> 00:18:52,722
the reality what we are showing.

242
00:18:54,173 --> 00:18:55,614
And the same goes for level design.

243
00:18:57,275 --> 00:18:59,296
If you are at war and you enter somebody's house,

244
00:18:59,557 --> 00:19:00,857
you're basically an intruder.

245
00:19:00,877 --> 00:19:03,599
You're not somebody who came to do a quest,

246
00:19:03,659 --> 00:19:04,880
so there are no quests in the game.

247
00:19:06,041 --> 00:19:08,563
You won't have people standing at the door and saying,

248
00:19:08,663 --> 00:19:09,864
oh, OK, great that you came.

249
00:19:09,884 --> 00:19:11,124
There are soldiers in the back.

250
00:19:11,184 --> 00:19:12,926
Please, you know, get rid of them.

251
00:19:13,406 --> 00:19:15,067
And there is also no treasure sometimes.

252
00:19:15,147 --> 00:19:17,989
There is a scene when we have a woman who

253
00:19:18,049 --> 00:19:20,591
is bullied by the soldier, and we can help them.

254
00:19:20,651 --> 00:19:20,791
But.

255
00:19:21,692 --> 00:19:25,495
If we help them, she runs away, she doesn't give us a diamond for doing that.

256
00:19:26,916 --> 00:19:30,558
So we also opted not to design walk-arounds in the game,

257
00:19:30,638 --> 00:19:38,344
so you cannot kind of satisfy both sides or do things without suffering some kind of cost.

258
00:19:40,366 --> 00:19:46,430
But we also chose, for example, not to have gore and violence as a way to build emotion,

259
00:19:46,911 --> 00:19:47,771
because we thought that...

260
00:19:49,513 --> 00:19:52,295
It's not the proper way to actually do that.

261
00:19:52,476 --> 00:19:55,558
It's more important to kind of have the feeling of grief,

262
00:19:55,638 --> 00:19:58,921
of the feeling of loss, of being helpless in a situation,

263
00:19:59,361 --> 00:20:05,427
instead of having pictures of scenes of war that we sometimes see in the movie,

264
00:20:07,088 --> 00:20:09,030
with really strong emotional impact.

265
00:20:09,350 --> 00:20:13,313
But a bit shallow in the term of game design.

266
00:20:14,314 --> 00:20:25,367
And finally, death is a valiant ending to this game. It's both the death of the people who are in your shelter as finishing the game by failing.

267
00:20:28,645 --> 00:20:33,447
A lot of these things seem kind of contradictory to some design rules or things that we are

268
00:20:33,587 --> 00:20:35,347
used to making games.

269
00:20:35,727 --> 00:20:37,628
And the question is, why all of that?

270
00:20:38,488 --> 00:20:39,208
Why we did that?

271
00:20:39,849 --> 00:20:46,050
And the answer, in my opinion, is we did that because we wanted to allow the player to have

272
00:20:46,110 --> 00:20:52,953
an experience of war as a civilian instead of giving them the opportunity to just win

273
00:20:52,993 --> 00:20:53,313
the game.

274
00:20:54,415 --> 00:20:59,028
Reading a good book with a moment of failure is also a great experience,

275
00:20:59,429 --> 00:21:01,895
and we try to kind of mimic that in this work of mine.

276
00:21:07,455 --> 00:21:18,537
So this experience, we also tried to create it via art of the game.

277
00:21:20,177 --> 00:21:31,400
So again a mood that I told you, so this bound, so everything art had to do was to amplify everything.

278
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:34,760
We also wanted to have a distinctive character of the game.

279
00:21:36,486 --> 00:21:40,249
have this message around the game and do it.

280
00:21:40,369 --> 00:21:42,511
So find the ways to do it for the small team

281
00:21:42,571 --> 00:21:45,113
that we were right back then.

282
00:21:45,153 --> 00:21:52,399
So first of all, when we wanted to create a style

283
00:21:52,439 --> 00:21:54,401
for the game, we wanted, you know,

284
00:21:54,921 --> 00:21:57,623
that's what I told you just a second ago.

285
00:21:57,663 --> 00:22:01,106
We wanted to amplify, we wanted to emphasize

286
00:22:01,567 --> 00:22:03,908
this situation the game was about,

287
00:22:03,949 --> 00:22:04,889
about the civilians.

288
00:22:06,451 --> 00:22:18,704
So we selected the colors, selected the palette of the game and we amplified the hopelessness,

289
00:22:18,824 --> 00:22:23,208
we amplified the serious situation you are then back there.

290
00:22:24,089 --> 00:22:36,135
Also, we wanted to create this, let's say, I sometimes call it drone reality, this situation

291
00:22:36,175 --> 00:22:41,438
when there is this look that is not...

292
00:22:42,822 --> 00:22:45,083
Realistical and not drawn.

293
00:22:45,323 --> 00:22:52,347
It is like we call it, like so we like to call it a novel.

294
00:22:52,367 --> 00:22:54,909
A novel look, just like reading a book.

295
00:22:55,329 --> 00:22:58,911
We were trying to push this approach of something to drawn,

296
00:22:59,251 --> 00:23:02,954
redrawn and drawn like a stories in this game.

297
00:23:03,814 --> 00:23:09,400
Also, we selected this view for the game to show the whole community.

298
00:23:09,520 --> 00:23:13,344
We wanted the player to not focus on the specific one character in the game.

299
00:23:13,604 --> 00:23:21,872
We wanted the player to see the whole community, the small community,

300
00:23:22,152 --> 00:23:26,256
and think of them as a whole and not to focus on one single person.

301
00:23:27,697 --> 00:23:33,319
So we had also inspiration for it, like what you see here is from Take On Me,

302
00:23:33,759 --> 00:23:37,401
or you can saw it in Dire Straits music videos.

303
00:23:38,341 --> 00:23:41,522
As you can see, it's also real and not real.

304
00:23:41,742 --> 00:23:47,685
We were trying to find this middle point with our art style.

305
00:23:48,465 --> 00:23:55,230
We also looked at how we can have this harsh look of the game, this contrasting harsh look of the game.

306
00:23:55,710 --> 00:24:01,114
One of the inspirations was what was Banksy doing, what he is right now doing with all the colors,

307
00:24:01,174 --> 00:24:11,000
so strong black and white and some small touch of color, some kind of mood creating approach that is, as I said, harsh.

308
00:24:12,847 --> 00:24:25,170
Also, we had a huge amount of research and we also used a lot of graffiti to communicate with the player.

309
00:24:26,151 --> 00:24:28,892
Because, you know, words are easy to understand.

310
00:24:30,960 --> 00:24:38,606
So, the style was one thing, but the true approach was, I think, even most important for us.

311
00:24:38,987 --> 00:24:44,571
Maybe it is not understandable by the player, but it was very important for us as a developer.

312
00:24:45,472 --> 00:24:51,217
Only this way we could really feel that, yes, we did it the right way.

313
00:24:51,757 --> 00:24:55,000
So, starting with the beginning.

